  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Zest 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong> (try to grate lightly and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter!)</p><p>Combine the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>, <strong>lemon zest</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]<strong> </span>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> on a plate and give everything a good mix up – these are your <strong>lemony breadcrumbs</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat the <strong>basa fillets</strong> dry with kitchen paper and add them to an oiled baking tray</p><p>Top with the <strong>lemony breadcrumbs</strong> and press them into the fish using the back of a spoon</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until the fish is cooked through and the breadcrumbs are golden</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Tip: If you'd rather skin-off mash, peel the potatoes first</p><p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiling water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> over a high heat and cook for 10-12 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, trim the ends off the <strong>spring onions</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>whole</strong> <strong>spring onions </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until they're soft and lightly browned</p><p>Once browned, transfer the <strong>spring onions</strong> to the same tray as the fish and reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat and add the <strong>clotted cream</strong></p><p>Pick the<strong> sage</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> from their stems, add them to the pan and cook for 1 min or until crispy</p><p>Once the clotted cream has melted, cut and juice the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> straight into the pan</p><p>Add the <strong>capers</strong> and remove the pan from the heat - this is your <strong>sage butter sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/803.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
